<p align="center"><font size="7">Changing an emoticon</font></p>
<p align="left"><font size="6">To change an emoticon you must first select which 
emotion you would like to change and then click the corresponding browse button.</font></p>
<p align="left">&nbsp;</p>
<p align="left"><font size="6">1. Lets change the happy, or &quot;online&quot; emoticon. 
Click browse and navigate to the image you wish to use to replace your current 
emoticon. It is import to remember that you can only select JPG, or JPEG images 
to replace emoticons. The FaceAlive implementation currently does not recognize 
Bitmap, or GIF images.</font></p>
<p align="left"><img border="0" src="page_712.jpg" width="508" height="360"></p>
<p align="left">&nbsp;</p>
<p align="left"><font size="6">2. Once you have selected the image you wish to 
replace your current emoticon with press the open button. The FaceAlive 
implementation will automatically resize your image to the proper size for you 
and store it in the temporary image store. All images that are updated reside in 
the temporary image store until you upload them to the Image Server.</font></p>
<p align="left"><img border="0" src="page_713.jpg" width="810" height="810"></p>
<p align="left">&nbsp;</p>
<p align="left"><font size="6">3. To make your new emoticon available to the 
classroom you must upload it to the image server.</font></p>

